(BREATHING SHAKILY)

56
00:07:31.362 --> 00:07:33.197
(HUNTERS CONTINUE GRUNTING)

57
00:07:40.404 --> 00:07:41.571
Stop!

58
00:07:48.044 --> 00:07:49.079
(GRUNTS)

59
00:07:53.016 --> 00:07:54.417
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

60
00:07:57.519 --> 00:07:58.755
(SIGHS)

61
00:08:00.657 --> 00:08:01.723
(SPEAKS IN SOLUTREAN)

62
00:08:01.725 --> 00:08:06.493
Stop. father. you stink!

63
00:08:06.495 --> 00:08:07.897
(BOTH LAUGH)

64
00:08:08.865 --> 00:08:11.531
You will hunt at my side.

65
00:08:11.533 --> 00:08:14.270
You are the chief's son.
My son.

66
00:08:30.786 --> 00:08:36.058
Prove you can lead.
Find your strength.

67
00:08:45.868 --> 00:08:47.870
(WOMAN CHANTING IN SOLUTREAN)

68
00:09:14.896 --> 00:09:16.731
(CHANTING CONTINUES)

69
00:09:33.181 --> 00:09:35.616
- (CONTINUES CHANTING)
- (FIRE CRACKLES)

70
00:10:04.345 --> 00:10:06.479
(SPEAKING IN SOLUTREAN)

71
00:10:06.481 --> 00:10:08.516
He is not ready.

72
00:10:11.985 --> 00:10:14.522
One season each year...

73
00:10:15.689 --> 00:10:18.058
...we hunt the Great Beast.

74
00:10:19.726 --> 00:10:22.496
We do this. or our tribe dies.

75
00:10:23.530 --> 00:10:27.868
He must do his part.

76
00:10:29.503 --> 00:10:33.373
Prove himself to the tribe.

77
00:10:36.409 --> 00:10:38.876
What if he can't...

78
00:10:38.878 --> 00:10:42.480
I love him
with my whole heart.

79
00:10:42.482 --> 00:10:46.717
He could die.
I am afraid.

80
00:10:46.719 --> 00:10:49.523
He leads with his heart.

81
00:10:50.823 --> 00:10:53.326
Not his spear.

82
00:10:54.093 --> 00:10:56.059
(SIGHS)

83
00:10:56.061 --> 00:10:58.063
(INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

84
00:11:13.112 --> 00:11:14.547
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

85
00:11:19.451 --> 00:11:20.886
(SOBBING)

86
00:11:38.604 --> 00:11:40.038
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

87
00:11:42.474 --> 00:11:43.640
(SPEAKS IN SOLUTREAN)

88
00:11:43.642 --> 00:11:45.477
Take this...
so nothing will harm you.

89
00:11:46.945 --> 00:11:48.813
I can take care of myself.

90
00:11:55.153 --> 00:11:56.421
Keda.

91
00:12:04.095 --> 00:12:06.462
(RHO SPEAKS)

92
00:12:06.464 --> 00:12:08.800
Know that I love you.

93
00:12:09.634 --> 00:12:11.069
(WIND HOWLING)

94
00:12:15.406 --> 00:12:17.273
(TAU SPEAKS)

95
00:12:17.275 --> 00:12:19.141
He will show us
that he is a man.

96
00:12:19.143 --> 00:12:20.443
Earn his place to lead.

97
00:12:20.445 --> 00:12:22.113
Then come home to you.

98
00:12:23.181 --> 00:12:26.351
You can't promise that.

99
00:12:27.518 --> 00:12:28.620
(SIGHS)

100
00:12:35.025 --> 00:12:36.293
Go.

101
00:12:44.968 --> 00:12:46.370
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

102
00:12:51.041 --> 00:12:52.276
(SOBBING SOFTLY)

103
00:12:58.148 --> 00:12:59.549
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

104
00:13:06.323 --> 00:13:07.691
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

105
00:13:21.471 --> 00:13:22.872
(BLOWING AIR)

106
00:13:25.041 --> 00:13:26.476
(FIRE CRACKLING)

107
00:13:29.211 --> 00:13:30.647
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

108
00:13:41.724 --> 00:13:43.492
(GRUNTING)

109
00:13:54.203 --> 00:13:55.237
(EXHALES)

110
00:13:55.837 --> 00:13:56.838
(GRUNTS)

111
00:13:59.608 --> 00:14:00.710
(GROANS)

112
00:14:13.922 --> 00:14:15.288
(CHUCKLES)

113
00:14:15.290 --> 00:14:16.490
(SPEAKING IN SOLUTREAN)

114
00:14:16.492 --> 00:14:20.059
To survive we must focus...
Be patient.

115
00:14:20.061 --> 00:14:22.061
We must not give up.

116
00:14:22.063 --> 00:14:24.530
(HUNTERS CHUCKLE)

117
00:14:24.532 --> 00:14:26.132
(BIRD CALLS)

118
00:14:26.134 --> 00:14:28.136
(INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

119
00:14:35.076 --> 00:14:36.478
(ANIMAL SCREECHES)

120
00:14:46.121 --> 00:14:47.589
(INDISTINCT CHATTER
IN SOLUTREAN)

121
00:14:56.897 --> 00:14:57.963
(SPEAKS IN SOLUTREAN)

122
00:14:57.965 --> 00:14:58.966
Father...

123
00:15:24.425 --> 00:15:26.160
(PANTING SOFTLY)

124
00:15:44.143 --> 00:15:45.444
(CHUCKLES)

125
00:15:45.446 --> 00:15:46.680
(SPEAKING IN SOLUTREAN)
My friend.

126
00:15:48.482 --> 00:15:49.982
(HUNTERS SPEAKING
IN SOLUTREAN)

127
00:15:52.985 --> 00:15:56.189
You have survived the winter.
A little fatter maybe?

128
00:15:57.557 --> 00:15:58.725
Yes.

129
00:16:00.026 --> 00:16:03.831
And I bring a young hunter...

130
00:16:05.364 --> 00:16:08.201
Raise your head...
and your eyes will follow.

131
00:16:13.206 --> 00:16:14.640
This is my son.

132
00:16:20.146 --> 00:16:22.415
Mine will not see
another hunt.

133
00:16:24.217 --> 00:16:26.184
He has gone
to the ancestors.

134
00:16:45.070 --> 00:16:48.273
You must be a proud father.

135
00:16:49.608 --> 00:16:52.742
I hope he makes me proud.

136
00:16:52.744 --> 00:16:54.579
- (BIRDS CHIRPING)
- (EXHALES)

137
00:17:01.954 --> 00:17:03.086
(TAU SPEAKING IN SOLUTREAN)

138
00:17:03.088 --> 00:17:05.255
Our tribe has walked
the Sacred Path

139
00:17:05.257 --> 00:17:07.292
Path since
the first Great Hunt.

140
00:17:08.460 --> 00:17:12.597
Marks guide our way.
Made by our ancestors.

141
00:17:18.904 --> 00:17:22.070
Left as a trail
for us to follow.

142
00:17:22.072 --> 00:17:25.042
And to help us survive
the great journey.

143
00:17:28.580 --> 00:17:31.816
Our hands point us
to the hunting ground.

144
00:17:32.751 --> 00:17:35.486
Some will return.

145
00:17:36.053 --> 00:17:38.455
Some will not.

146
00:17:40.491 --> 00:17:44.493
Those marks remain... for the
leader to bring the hunters home.

147
00:17:44.495 --> 00:17:46.330
(CROWS CAWING)

148
00:17:49.066 --> 00:17:51.602
- (INSECTS BUZZING)
- (HUNTERS SPEAKING SOLUTREAN)

149
00:17:57.308 --> 00:17:58.509
(BOAR CHUFFING)

150
00:18:05.649 --> 00:18:06.984
- (GRUNTS)
- (BOAR SCREECHES)

151
00:18:07.651 --> 00:18:10.084
(BOAR SQUEALING)

152
00:18:10.086 --> 00:18:11.185
(SPEAKING IN SOLUTREAN)

153
00:18:11.187 --> 00:18:12.288
Finish it.

154
00:18:13.323 --> 00:18:14.758
(SQUEALING CONTINUES)

155
00:18:38.381 --> 00:18:39.816
(CONTINUES SQUEALING)

156
00:18:45.989 --> 00:18:47.156
(GRUNTS)

157
00:18:50.460 --> 00:18:53.228
You take a life
to give life to your tribe.

158
00:18:54.030 --> 00:18:56.797
Do it. Now.

159
00:18:56.799 --> 00:18:58.233
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

160
00:19:03.372 --> 00:19:04.506
I'm sorry!

161
00:19:06.676 --> 00:19:08.077
- (GRUNTS)
- (SQUEALING STOPS)

162
00:19:11.146 --> 00:19:13.116
Life is for the strong!

163
00:19:16.318 --> 00:19:19.254
It is earned. not given.

164
00:19:23.059 --> 00:19:24.493
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

165
00:19:27.896 --> 00:19:29.898
(INDISTINCT CHATTER.
CHUCKLING)

166
00:19:38.172 --> 00:19:39.239
(TWIG SNAPS)

167
00:19:39.241 --> 00:19:40.876
(HUNTERS LAUGHING)

168
00:19:41.510 --> 00:19:43.345
(RUSTLING)

169
00:19:46.313 --> 00:19:47.381
(SHUSHING)

170
00:19:49.216 --> 00:19:50.282
(TWIG SNAPS)

171
00:19:50.284 --> 00:19:51.787
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

172
00:20:00.095 --> 00:20:01.395
(GROWLING)

173
00:20:11.706 --> 00:20:12.972
(TWIGS SNAP)

174
00:20:12.974 --> 00:20:14.408
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

175
00:20:19.046 --> 00:20:20.746
(SPEAKING IN SOLUTREAN)

176
00:20:20.748 --> 00:20:22.416
Be calm.

177
00:20:32.560 --> 00:20:33.961
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

178
00:20:52.345 --> 00:20:54.581
Stay alert.

179
00:20:59.486 --> 00:21:00.988
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

180
00:21:10.764 --> 00:21:12.866
- (GROWLING)
- (HUNTERS SCREAMING)

181
00:21:14.834 --> 00:21:17.335
- (KAPPA SCREAMING)
- (ANIMAL GROWLING)

182
00:21:17.337 --> 00:21:18.669
- (ANIMAL CHUFFS)
- (FANGS SLASHING FLESH)

183
00:21:18.671 --> 00:21:20.106
(SCREAMING STOPS)

184
00:21:20.874 --> 00:21:22.006
(ANIMAL BELLOWS)

185
00:21:22.008 --> 00:21:23.843
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

186
00:21:25.310 --> 00:21:27.147
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

187
00:21:30.183 --> 00:21:31.618
(PANTING)

188
00:21:32.652 --> 00:21:34.685
He is gone...

189
00:21:34.687 --> 00:21:38.622
...but we must stay strong.

190
00:21:38.624 --> 00:21:40.026
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

191
00:21:43.695 --> 00:21:45.129
(TAU SPEAKING IN SOLUTREAN)

192
00:21:45.131 --> 00:21:47.133
May his spirit
watch over the Path...

193
00:21:48.201 --> 00:21:51.868
...as his ancestors
before him.

194
00:21:51.870 --> 00:21:53.305
(INSECTS BUZZING)

195
00:22:20.732 --> 00:22:22.567
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

196
00:22:27.005 --> 00:22:29.074
- (BIRDS CHIRPING)
- (TWIG SNAPS)

197
00:22:29.707 --> 00:22:31.243
(HUNTERS GRUNTING)

198
00:22:33.178 --> 00:22:35.280
(ANIMALS HOWLING.
CHITTERING IN DISTANCE)

199
00:22:38.950 --> 00:22:40.118
(KEDA GRUNTS)

200
00:22:45.590 --> 00:22:47.290
(ANIMAL ROARING)

201
00:22:47.292 --> 00:22:48.893
(SHUSHING)

202
00:22:53.598 --> 00:22:55.433
(BIRD SCREECHING IN DISTANCE)

203
00:23:00.471 --> 00:23:01.706
(BIRD SCREECHING)

204
00:23:06.443 --> 00:23:07.612
(BIRD SCREECHES)

205
00:23:49.819 --> 00:23:51.254
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

206
00:23:59.329 --> 00:24:00.594
(TAU SPEAKS IN SOLUTREAN)

207
00:24:00.596 --> 00:24:04.433
The stone markers
guide you during the day.

208
00:24:06.669 --> 00:24:12.206
Now you bear the marks...

209
00:24:12.208 --> 00:24:15.978
...that will guide you
at night.

210
00:24:22.952 --> 00:24:24.787
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

211
00:24:33.028 --> 00:24:36.031
The light
from our ancestors...

212
00:24:38.033 --> 00:24:41.136
...showing us the way home.

213
00:24:45.975 --> 00:24:47.142
(EXHALES)

214
00:24:47.575 --> 00:24:49.508
Home.

215
00:24:49.510 --> 00:24:51.347
(WOLF HOWLING)

216
00:24:55.217 --> 00:24:57.217
You see that one?

217
00:24:57.219 --> 00:25:00.089
That is the Alpha.
their leader.

218
00:25:06.362 --> 00:25:11.165
The Alpha must care for his pack.
Above all else.

219
00:25:13.835 --> 00:25:17.770
But he is also
always in danger.

220
00:25:17.772 --> 00:25:19.774
(INDISTINCT CHATTER
AND LAUGHTER)

221
00:25:21.676 --> 00:25:27.413
Others in the pack
will challenge him...

222
00:25:27.415 --> 00:25:28.850
(WOLVES CONTINUE HOWLING)

223
00:25:30.918 --> 00:25:34.253
...if they sense weakness.

224
00:25:34.255 --> 00:25:37.056
The Alpha lets the others
know his place...

225
00:25:37.058 --> 00:25:39.593
...with his strength and calm.

226
00:25:43.131 --> 00:25:47.400
He was not born the Alpha.

227
00:25:47.402 --> 00:25:52.639
But he earned it with his courage...
and his heart.

228
00:25:55.108 --> 00:25:57.110
(INSECTS TRILLING. BUZZING)

229
00:26:13.727 --> 00:26:14.993
Shh.

230
00:26:14.995 --> 00:26:17.130
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

231
00:26:24.104 --> 00:26:25.272
(SNIFFING)

232
00:26:26.073 --> 00:26:28.175
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

233
00:26:45.658 --> 00:26:47.660
(INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

234
00:26:54.600 --> 00:26:56.001
(GRUNTING SOFTLY)

235
00:26:59.805 --> 00:27:01.207
(HUNTERS PANTING)

236
00:27:05.277 --> 00:27:07.277
(PANTING)

237
00:27:07.279 --> 00:27:09.213
- (BISON SNORTING)
- (INSECT BUZZING)

238
00:27:09.215 --> 00:27:10.648
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

239
00:27:31.170 --> 00:27:32.369
(SPEAKS IN SOLUTREAN)

240
00:27:32.371 --> 00:27:33.539
Go!

241
00:27:35.508 --> 00:27:36.806
(BISON ROAR)

242
00:27:36.808 --> 00:27:37.809
(HUNTERS YELL)

243
00:27:41.980 --> 00:27:42.981
(BISON ROAR)

244
00:27:44.550 --> 00:27:45.848
(GASPS)

245
00:27:45.850 --> 00:27:46.851
(CHUFFING)

246
00:27:48.419 --> 00:27:49.420
(GROWLING)

247
00:27:54.025 --> 00:27:55.026
(YELLS)

248
00:28:00.198 --> 00:28:01.998
(HUNTERS YELLING)

249
00:28:02.000 --> 00:28:03.399
TAU: Keda!

250
00:28:03.401 --> 00:28:05.334
(HUNTERS CLAMORING)

251
00:28:05.336 --> 00:28:06.768
Keda!

252
00:28:06.770 --> 00:28:08.337
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

253
00:28:08.339 --> 00:28:10.439
Keda!

254
00:28:10.441 --> 00:28:12.508
(TAU SPEAKING IN SOLUTREAN)
Do not look down!

255
00:28:12.510 --> 00:28:13.742
(SPEAKS IN SOLUTREAN)

256
00:28:13.744 --> 00:28:16.011
(BREATHING RAPIDLY)

257
00:28:16.013 --> 00:28:18.216
Don't let go!

258
00:28:19.384 --> 00:28:20.784
(INAUDIBLE)

259
00:28:24.355 --> 00:28:25.856
(KEDA SCREAMING)

260
00:28:29.126 --> 00:28:30.459
(GRUNTS)

261
00:28:30.461 --> 00:28:32.062
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

262
00:28:33.030 --> 00:28:36.433
TAU: (ECHOING) Keda!

263
00:28:41.639 --> 00:28:43.440
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

264
00:28:43.941 --> 00:28:45.375
(GRUNTING)

265
00:28:49.745 --> 00:28:51.379
(SPEAKING IN SOLUTREAN)

266
00:28:51.381 --> 00:28:53.048
My friend...

267
00:28:53.050 --> 00:28:54.685
(BREATHING RAPIDLY)

268
00:28:55.285 --> 00:28:57.154
